"Faded" é uma verdadeira obra-prima que toca a alma e faz com que nos conectemos de maneira profunda com a música. Thank you Alan Walker for masterpieces❤❤❤

comment_text:
The song "Faded" by Alan Walker is a popular electronic dance music track with lyrics that express a sense of loss, loneliness, and yearning. The following is a line-by-line analysis of the song:

"You were the shadow to my light
Did you feel us?
Another star
You fade away
Afraid our aim is out of sight
Wanna see us
Alight"

These lyrics express the feeling of a relationship that has ended or faded away, leaving the speaker feeling alone and uncertain about the future. The "shadow" to the speaker's "light" suggests that the other person was a complementary presence in their life. The speaker wonders if the other person also felt the connection that they did, but ultimately they faded away, and the speaker is left feeling lost and unsure of their direction.

"Where are you now?
Where are you now?
Where are you now?
Was it all in my fantasy?
Where are you now?
Were you only imaginary?"

These lines express the speaker's longing for the other person and the confusion about whether their connection was real or just imagined. The repetition of the question "Where are you now?" suggests that the speaker is searching for answers and trying to make sense of their feelings. The last line questions whether the relationship was ever real, or if it was just a figment of the speaker's imagination.

"Where are you now?
Atlantis
Under the sea
Under the sea
Where are you now?
Another dream
The monster's running wild inside of me
I'm faded
I'm faded
So lost, I'm faded
I'm faded
So lost, I'm faded"

These lyrics use the metaphor of the lost city of Atlantis to represent the speaker's feelings of being lost and disconnected from the world around them. The "monster" running wild inside of them suggests that they are struggling with inner turmoil and emotional pain. The repeated refrain "I'm faded" reinforces the sense of being lost and disconnected from reality.

"These shallow waters never met what I needed
I'm letting go a deeper dive
Eternal silence of the sea, I'm breathing
Alive"

These lines suggest that the shallow relationships and experiences in the speaker's life have left them feeling unfulfilled. The metaphor of diving deeper represents the speaker's desire to explore more meaningful connections and experiences. The "eternal silence of the sea" suggests a peaceful and calming presence that the speaker finds comfort in, and the final word "alive" expresses the hope that they can find a sense of purpose and meaning in their life.

"Under the bright but faded lights
You've set my heart on fire
Where are you now?
Where are you now?"

These lines express the speaker's continued longing for the other person, and the intense emotional connection that they once shared. The "bright but faded lights" suggest a sense of nostalgia for the past, and the imagery of a heart on fire represents the passion and intensity of their relationship. The repetition of the question "Where are you now?" emphasizes the speaker's continued sense of loss and longing.

In summary, "Faded" by Alan Walker is a song about a lost or fading relationship and the speaker's feelings of loneliness, confusion, and longing. The lyrics use metaphors of light and darkness, the lost city of Atlantis, and diving deeper to explore the speaker's emotions and desire for connection and meaning.

comment_text: У меня папа вел род от самых старших братьев от Ноя, так что я самый старший брат на земле, ещё поэтому может погода зависит от состояния моего организма. Старших надо слушаться , а о младших заботиться, это основное правило семьи на земле. Я к сожалению не о ком не научился ни заботиться , ни папу неслушался, хотя он меня и не заставлял ничего делать, только заботился и спрашивал чего я хочу и мы старались по возможности это сделать, как мне его не хватает. Если бы люди относились к друг другу с уважением, это было бы прекрасно, представляешь как ко мне относятся все младшие братья, если бы они знали кто я или был мой папа, вообщем это тоже не важно, ведь Иисус Христос вот что важно он наш Бог и Царь и Патриарх и Спаситель и Дарователь вечной жизни, а все остальное уже не важно, но чисто по человечески можно было бы и уважить старшего брата, чтоб ему не было плохо, ведь в этом нет ничего постыдного, а старшим будет приятно заботиться о младших кто уважает их. Жаль что на земле скрыто родство никто не знает кто кому приходиться и какой народ от каких братьев ведёт свой род и старшинство.Ведь младшие братья скрыли старшинство, чтоб могли взять старшинство которое им не принадлежит, и тем самым это выглядит как чтец в шапке митрополита.Ведь младшие не могут позаботиться о старших потому что они должны их слушаться, а старшие не могут позаботиться о младших потому что не считают себя старшими и тем самым не могут выполнить обязанности старшинства.От сюда столько проблем.Мой род являеться старшим для всех народов, но живёт в России в Санкт-Петербурге, почему так выбрал Бог неизвестно почему среди именно русского народа, а не какого-то другого народа.Но как видишь , меня все ненавидят и говорят что я гордый, но я не знаю как относиться зная это, и как ко мне относятся они не зная этого.Вот поэтому от незнания каждого из нас своего места в старшинстве и рождает неуважение зависть и гордость, если бы все знали старшинство, то старшие заботились о младших добровольно а младшим слушались старших с уважением.Потомучто каждый знал свое родовое старшинство.Так что я являюсь уникальным человеком на земле, если я умру то может наступить конец света так как отнимиться удерживающий, как было во времена Адама когда не стало последнего из самых старших сынов Каина наступил потоп, а сейчас все будет сожжено.

Payment = (Number of views / 1000) x Payment per view

So, if YouTube pays $50 for 1000 views, it would pay $170 million for 3.4 billion views.

comment_text:
Me before listening to this song: 
I’ve never cried in my life (not even when I was born, my mother provided proof as well).

Me after listening to this song: 
*starts bawling my eyes out*

My friend: 
Are you okay?

*song replays*

Him: 
*does the same*

Both of our girlfriends at the time: 
*walk into the room* 
Why are you guys crying?

*song replays again*

Them: 
*look at each other* 
*look at us* 
*pause while listening to the song* 
*start crying as well*

I’m not even kidding, this is an entirely true story, no words besides just asking if I was okay and why we were crying at first, then we all just stared at each other. This is the most amazing song I’ve ever heard, and the story with it is even better. I will never stop listening to this.

comment_text: Do you know what's weird about this song? It's not actually about the song but when it was used and how it is now perceived back then you usually heard the song in really shitty sfm's and gotcha animations and people made fun of it because of that now we're back here again Reminiscing on when there was no covid where our mental health wasn't in the dumpster when we actually had good friends and now we're living in a world where everything is flipped upside down it's sort of nostalgic in a way I view it as a time capsule within a period when I was beginning to get into FNAF when FNAF 2 was the biggest thing to ever exist when I was a genuinely happy kid and not having to worry about money how my parents are doing and how the people around me are doing or rather the degree of what that was it's comforting yet distant it means that we're growing up and yet I never wanted to I never wanted to grow up and live as a teenager with rampant hormones and a crumbling mental state and yet here we are

comment_text:
Whenever I hear this song I can feel this situation. I saw her after 2.5 years in Beleghata, Kolkata in opposite side of road on 5th March, 2022 at exact 5:55pm.... 
I feel my eyes are being wet slowly, I kept the tears hidden & just looking at her.
My heartbeat was much higher than normal, my chest was throbbing, I was sweating profusely, I felt like my blood pressure was rising. Ufff!! This feeling mannnn I can't explain... One of the best feeling for me... 
Every night, every time whenever I see her photo, I see her with another boy, I just close my eyes, kept tears hidden, I smile and think that I have lost one of the most important person/thing in my life for my own mistake and it hurts the most.
I know now it's already too late to understand that It was totally my fault.. I will regret it for the rest of my life & I have to accept it.. She was not my 1st or 2nd option, she was my one and only option for me. I realized her value after losing her..
But thank God for giving her in my life, I couldn't understand her value that's my fault & thanks to her for changing me indirectly even after break up. I know now I am waiting for her and may be that isn't never going to happen but still I will love her & remember her for the rest of my life that's my promise to myself. It's almost 3 years still I can't move on from this, may be I don't wanna move on from her🙂.... 
One sided love is really unconditional. No explanation, nothing in return just pure love. Yessss!! It hurts, no doubt. But nothing can be as beautiful as this feeling.. Thank you so much God for giving me this type of feeling, this type of love for her even after losing her, I will be very greatful to you... I have no complaint to anyone... 🙂
"Long Live Love"....!! 🖤

Мне тяжело.

Я знаю это.

Смотри, как это просто.
Сегодня я отрезала ещё одну.
Все чувства уместились в одно место.

Прости.
Прощай.

comment_text: In those years from 2014 to 2019, it was when the world was different and beautiful, now nothing is the same, it is super different, before we could listen and say outdoors, everything we felt, listening to this beautiful song, made me remember all the moments i had to go through, to get to right now, these types of songs always make me feel happy and sad at the same time, i will never get tired of listening to this beauty of song, it was literally half of my childhood, we have been wanting to travel again for those feelings and special moments of our life, just to be and continue on this course to safe home, forever, I wish everything were like this today, I miss those most special years of life, that I want to go back a thousand times more Now they are not the same feelings as before but I am learning to accept everything, even the new changes and stop making my life sad, because of the memories that the songs make me feel, even the photos, videos or something else that makes me think about a moment of my childhood, nothing stays the same as before, I love these sensations characterized by their different emotions very much, this song came at a beautiful moment, I love it forever, This song will age like wine. It gets better as you get older, as time goes by and everything changes, we've revolutionized in just a few years, I still remember, 6 years ago, after school, or right there, always listening to this song with no worries, no pressure, no certain viruses outside. just enjoy a beautiful life, even if it's not the same right now, I'm grateful to be alive and to be able to comment on everything I wanted to tell you my dear Alan, I love you, late but sure, I will love Faded forever, ily Alan Walker, I have loved this song since it came out, until recently I still love it, just as much as the first time, this is amazing, This is good music, thank you 😊💖
